Slower through the air, full, around middle. Alex Carey tries to sweep this but the ball goes off the top edge over the keeper and towards fine leg. Three taken!
Around the off pole, pitches it up. Cameron Green drives but finds the fielder at short cover. Good over for Australia! 11 runs off it.
There is the sweep again! Tad quicker now, around 87 clicks, tossed up, around the leg pole. Alex Carey hits it through square leg. Asitha Fernando makes a good stop there! Two taken.
Outside off, fuller one. Alex Carey leans forward and blocks it towards cover.
Beaten this time! Ramesh Mendis serves this quicker, outside off, full. Alex Carey looks to sweep this one but he fails to get any bat on it this time. That wasn't too far from the off pole.
Drifting it on the pads. Alex Carey sweeps it towards short fine leg.
Outside off, fuller one. Alex Carey presses forward and defends it towards cover.
Close one! Ramesh Mendis this time pulls his length ball, serves a flatter one, around off. Alex Carey stays back and tries to cut this one but he gets an inside edge just away from the leg pole.

Bye! Some swing there for Asitha Fernando! He starts off with a fuller one, swinging down the leg side. Cameron Green looks to flick but he misses. Niroshan Dickwella dives towards his left, but the ball deflects off his left glove and goes towards fine leg. The batters steal a bye!
FOUR! Top shot! Pitches it up, wide of off. Alex Carey drives this uppishly but away from the fielder at covers for a boundary.
Another fuller one, outside off. Alex Carey drives again but finds the fielder at the cover region on this occasion.
FOUR! In the gap this time! Similar delivery pitched up and wide of off. Alex Carey once again creams his drive, through covers, for a boundary.
On a length now, outside off. Alex Carey pushes it to the fielder at covers.
Tad fuller again, outside off. Alex Carey once again drives and finds the fielder at extra-cover. 9 runs off Asitha Fernando's first over on Day 2!
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Cameron Green defends it back towards the bowler.
Another one on middle with some turn, Cameron Green eases it towards the fielder at silly mid on.
Goes fuller down the middle, Cameron Green guides it towards the off side but straight towards the cover fielder.
This one lands on middle and fuller, Cameron Green sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Shorter one outside off, Alex Carey goes on the back foot and cuts it away towards the backward point region.
Bowls it fuller and on leg, Alex Carey sweeps it towards the square leg for one.

Asitha Fernando goes around the wicket and bowls this full and outside off, Alex Carey hits this hard towards covers. The cover fielder dives to his right and a half stop allows the batters to run two.
Short delivery angled into the batter. Alex Carey pulls but mistimes it and gets a top edge. The ball falls into the vacant square leg region for a single.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Cameron Green gets on top of this and defends solidly.
Fuller and on middle, a hint of reverse there as Green flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Wide! Asitha Fernando digs it in short but it goes way over the head of the batter.
Back of a length, around leg, Carey fails to glance and it goes off his thigh pad to square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Yorker around off, Green digs it out safely.

FOUR LEG BYES! Goes fuller on middle, spinning away from the batter with extra bounce, Alex Carey looks to swing at it but misses. The keeper misses it as well it bounces past his left shoulder. The ball races behind for a boundary. The 50-run stand comes up!
Lands it on middle and fuller in length, Alex Carey sweeps it but finds the fielder at leg gully.
Skidding down the leg side, Alex Carey tries to sweep but misses. He is hit on the pads, they appeal but to no avail.
Bowls it on leg and fuller in length, Alex Carey flicks it towards the fielder at backward square leg.
Tossed-up delivery, Alex Carey looks to sweep at it but misses as the ball goes straight into the gloves of the keeper.
FOUR! Australia lead by 1 run now. Fuller in length around middle, Alex Carey sits down on one knee and sweeps it firmly through square leg for a boundary.
Asitha Fernando starts this over well. Good-length delivery angling in from outside off. Cameron Green defends this one back down the pitch.
Fraction fuller this time angling into the pads, Cameron Green flicks this towards the mid-wicket fielder who parries it towards mid on.
Full once again on middle, Cameron Green gets this wide of mid on for a single.
Around the wicket to the left-hander, bowled on a good length and angling away, Alex Carey plays this towards gully.
Short delivery this time but wide from off stump. Alex Carey initially shapes up to pull this but changes his mind at the last moment.
WIDE! Goes even shorter but on a good line. The square leg umpire says it is too high and wide has been called.

FOUR! Alex Carey almost guides this towards the slip fielder! The ball moves away from the batter from a good length, Alex Carey tries to work this fine for a single but gets a thick edge that makes the ball fly closer to the slip fielder than he had anticipated! The slip fielder dives to his left but does not reach it as the ball reaches the boundary to add four runs to the lead!
Goes fuller and outside off, Cameron Green drives it towards long off for one.
This one lands outside off as well, Alex Carey sweeps it towards backward square leg for a single again.
Bowls it on middle with some turn, Cameron Green waits for the ball and guides it to deep point for a brace.
Goes outside off again, this is again guided towards deep point for a couple of runs.

Shout for an lbw, not given. A googly by Jeffrey Vandersay, it lands on a fuller length around middle and beats the forward defense of Green. It pings him on the pads, they appeal but the umpire stays still. Missing leg. Too much turn there.
FOUR! Goes fuller and down the leg side, Cameron Green uses his feet and flicks it sharply through mid-wicket for a boundary. The lead moves to 17 now.

FOUR! Alex Carey has looked wonderful in this innings! Lasith Embuldeniya tosses this one full on off, Alex Carey connects with his reverse sweep powerfully as the ball races to the deep point boundary! He reaches his 40s in no time!
Flighted full once again, Alex Carey paddles this but straight to the short fine leg fielder.

Bang on the helmet! Alex Carey is using the reverse sweep as his go-to shot! This is a fraction shorter outside off, Alex Carey misses the line of the ball as it spins and crashes into the grille of his helmet. If not for the helmet, Carey could have lost his front teeth.
Alex Carey comes down the wicket and plays the ball on the full, back towards the bowler.
Alex Carey attempts the reverse sweep once again but this time the ball is not as full and towards leg, he manages to get a faint edge that makes the ball go away from the stumps.
Flighted full and on middle, Alex Carey strides forward and defends firmly.
Starts with a shorter one on leg, Cameron Green leaves it alone.
Shorter one again, Cameron Green ducks underneath it.
Sticks to bowling it shorter and on middle, Cameron Green ducks under it again.
This one lands slightly shorter and on middle, Cameron Green looks to defend it but the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the off side.
Sticks to bowling it shorter again, Cameron Green ducks under it and lets it through and towards the keeper.
Back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Cameron Green eases it back towards the bowler. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Australia and Alex Carey are up and running in the final session! Fuller one, around middle. Alex Carey reverse-sweeps it towards point for a single.
Full from over the wicket now, around middle. Cameron Green defends this one but the ball goes off the inside edge and falls short of forward short leg.
Outside off, a tad shorter. Cameron Green cuts it towards point.
Pitches it up, on middle. Cameron Green defends it out.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Cameron Green advances down the track and tries to defend but he misses. The ball hits his pads and lobs up towards short leg.
Swing and a miss! Fuller, around middle and leg. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses.
Pitches this one up, around middle and leg, angling in. Alex Carey tries to flick this one but he manages to get a slight inside edge back onto his pads and towards fine eg. A single taken!
A loud appeal for caught behind, but the umpire says no! Asitha Fernando drops it short now, around the leg pole. Cameron Green tries to pull this but he fails to get any bat on it.
Asitha Fernando hits the deck hard again, serves it short, around middle and leg. Cameron Green ducks underneath it.
Shorter one, around middle and off. Cameron Green ducks and lets that go through to the keeper.
On a length, darting on the pads. Cameron Green hangs back and tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, angling this one in, around middle and leg. Alex Carey flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Cameron Green brings up his fifty in style! It's been a classy knock so far. Fuller one, around off. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and sweeps it powerfully through mid-wicket for a boundary. He will want to convert this into a big one!
Another fuller ball, around middle and leg. Cameron Green sweeps once again this time towards deep square leg for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's a fine running catch by Dinesh Chandimal. The 84-run stand has been broken and Sri Lanka can take a huge sigh of relief. Ramesh Mendis hurls it across on a fuller length, around off and turning away, Alex Carey attempts for a big heave across the line but due to the away spin, the ball catches the toe end of his bat and flies behind mid off. Dinesh Chandimal scoots behind, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a very good catch as he goes down. Australia lead by 29 runs.
Howout: c Dinesh Chandimal b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: FOUR! That's a good shot! Too full in length and outside off, Cameron Green uses his feet to reach the pitch of the ball and drills it through covers.
Uses his feet again and this time plays a full ball from the inner half of his bat. The ball runs down to long on and they cross.
Play and a miss. Floated delivery, landing full around middle and spinning away, Starc draws forward to defend but it whistles past the outside edge.
Skiddy delivery, full and down the leg side, Green attempts to flick off his pads but misses. Niroshan Dickwella dives across to his left and collects the ball.
Slower bouncer around leg with a leg gully in place, Cameron Green reads the plan and ducks.
Back of a length, around leg, Green helps it from the back foot to square leg and collects a single.
Asitha Fernando eyes the blockhole, Starc does well to dig it out towards mid on. Has he broken his bat? Yes.
Bang on the helmet! A sharp bouncer, around middle and skidding into the batter, Starc takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to get away. He fails and is hit on the helmet.
Shortish and around leg, Starc tries to work it around but misses. It goes behind the wickets off his body.
Fuller and around off, Green drives it down to long off for a single.
Edged but safe! Loopy delivery, full and around off, Starc tries to defend off the front foot but it spins away to take the outside edge. It doesn't carry to first slip.
Fuller and on off, defended back.
FOUR! Poor delivery. Short in length and wide outside off, Mitchell Starc immediately goes on the back foot and whacks it through cover-point. Opens his account.
Slower through the air but it lands in the blackhole, Starc digs it out as a spray of dust comes off the pitch.
Leans forward to a full ball around off and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Delivers it on a length and around leg, Green clips it to square leg and rotates the strike.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Green tries to help it away off his pads but misses.
Beaten! A little bit of late away movement there, perhaps some reverse movement, on a length and outside off, Green pushes inside the line and misses.
This one skids into the batter with the angle, on middle, Green bunts it to mid on and picks up a single.
Quite wide outside off to bother the batter, Starc offers no shot.
FOUR! Embuldeniya continues to leak boundaries. Too full in length and drifting down the leg side, Green goes down and sweeps it delightfully to the deep backward square leg fence.
IN THE AIR... Falls safely. Loopy and full, around leg, Green again tries to sweep but it takes the top half of his bat. The ball flies to deep square leg and drops safely. They take one.
Fuller and on off, Starc tries to defend and does so off the inner half to short mid-wicket.
Fires it full and around leg, Starc sweeps and it deflects off short leg to mid-wicket. They cross.
Fullish and on off, Green runs down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and flighted, around off, Green walks forward and drives it towards short cover. The fielder there makes a partial stop.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Starc defends it off his front foot.
Short and wide outside off, Starc goes back and flashes his bat at it. Connects only with thin air.
Much fuller this time, around leg, Starc digs it out from the outer half of his blade. The ball rolls to short third man and they cross. AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 50 RUNS!
Flighted and around off, spinning in, Green walks down the track and defends it off the inner edge to silly mid on.

FOUR! The Australians are finding ways to score runs. Loopy delivery, full and spinning down the leg side, Green attempts to play the conventional sweep but it takes the back of his bat and runs down to third man for a boundary.
Advances down the track and defends a full ball back to the bowler. Ramesh Mendis has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Spinning down the leg side, it's pushed quicker through the air, Starc leaves it alone.
Tossed up around off, fuller in length, it's defended back to the bowler.
Allows the ball to spin back in from around off and helps it to short mid-wicket.
Flatter through the air, around off and turning in, Starc goes on the back foot and hits it past short mid-wicket for a single.
Excellent shot! Full and wide outside off, Green goes down and sweeps it all along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and outside off, spinning in sharply, Starc presses forward to drive but it takes the inner edge and goes to short mid-wicket.
Drifting in around off, fuller in length, Green comes down the track and forces it to long off for a single.
Beautiful! Lovely drift into the batter, landing on a fuller length around off and turning square, Starc is forward in defense but gets beaten.
Quicker and shorter on off, Starc goes on the back foot and punches it to covers.
Beaten again. Spinning away from the batter, Starc tries to defend but misses again due to the away spin.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.

FOUR BYES! Brilliant delivery but no reward for the bowler. It's nicely tossed up, landing full and around off, Mitchell Starc tries to play straight but gets beaten. It misses the off stump by a whisker and stays low as well to go through the legs of the keeper.
Lasith Embuldeniya goes over the wicket to the right-hander. Pitches it a fraction short outside leg, Cameron Green punches it back to the bowler.
Flighted full outside leg, Cameron Green gets to the pitch of the delivery and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly short and spinning in from outside off, Mitchell Starc goes back into the crease and punches it through covers for one run.
Really wide down the leg side and full, Cameron Green tries to sweep but misses.
Lasith Embuldeniya continues bowling outside leg and full. Cameron Green puts his pad to this one.
Full once again outside leg stump, Cameron Green gets back and knocks it towards long on for a single.
Fuller and on the middle, Green steps out and defends it back towards the bowler.
A bit short and on leg, Green pulls it of his back foot towards deep square leg for a single.
Slower through the air on off, Starc pushes it to deep backward point for a run.
Quicker and full outside off, Green uses his feet but finds the bowler again.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis gets rid of a well-set batter here! He grabs his fourth wicket of the game and Australia have lost their seventh. A much-needed wicket for Sri Lanka! Cameron Green departs after an exceptional knock. A loopy ball, this one lands around off and spins in sharply. Cameron Green gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire raises his finger! Cameron Green opts for a review! No bat is involved, confirms the UltraEdge, and the Ball Tracking shows three reds. Cameron Green has to walk back. Pat Cummins is the new man in!
Howout: lbw b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Full and on the middle, Cummins blocks it off his back foot. A successful over for the Sri Lankans.
Jeffrey Vandersay starts off with a full delivery spinning in from outside off, Mitchell Starc tries to slog but misses the line of the ball.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Jeffrey Vandersay comes into the attack and strikes right away! Full delivery outside off, Mitchell Starc aims for a heave across the line but ends up dragging it off the inner half, straight to the left of the bowler, who dives and takes a lovely catch with both his hands. Flings the ball in the air in celebration and Sri Lanka are looking to run through the tail.
Howout: c & b Jeffrey Vandersay

Commentary: Slightly shorter and outside off. Nathan Lyon attempts to sweep this time but misses.
Nathan Lyon is off the mark with a sweep shot. Jeffrey Vandersay bowls this full on off, Nathan Lyon connects this time and gets a single to backward square leg.
Shorter one, around middle. Pat Cummins stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Tosses this one up, full, and around the leg pole. Pat Cummins leans and blocks it out watchfully.
Quicker length delivery on middle, Lyon manages to defend it back to the bowler.
A bit full outside off, Lyon tries to play it on the off side but it hits the inside edge of his bat and goes to short leg.
A bit short on the middle, turning in. Lyon tries to play at it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Shout for LBW but the finger remains down.
On a length and on the middle, Lyon slogsweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Shorter one on middle, Pat Cummins flicks it towards fine leg for one.
FOUR! Fuller one down the leg side, Nathan Lyon gets on his knees and sweeps it past backward square leg for a boundary.
Flighted full on off, Pat Cummins goes for a big shot but only manages an inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Attempts the sweep but misses, Full and turning in from wide outside off and strikes the batsman on his legs. Brief appeal but the ball is clearly hitting outside the line of the stumps.
Nathan Lyon gets a stride forward and plays the full delivery outside off towards cover for a single.

SIX! Pat Cummins gets a hold of this one! Jeffrey Vandersay feeds the batter with a flighted delivery, full and on middle. Pat Cummins thumps this straight and really high up right behind the bowler for a biggie! Useful runs here for Australia.
Full once again outside off. Pat Cummins tries to play for the turn but the ball keeps its line and beats the outside edge.
Googly this time from Jeffrey Vandersay from outside off, Pat Cummins gets well behind the line of the ball and defends.
Fuller delivery on off, Lyon sweeps it but it hits his foot and the ball stays on the pitch. It looks like he is hurt a bit.
Tossed up on middle, Lyon goes down and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a run.
On a length outside off, Cummins leans and drives it to long off. They take a single.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, turning in, Lyon goes down for the sweep but the ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg. They get a single.
A bit short and around leg, Cummins flicks it of his back foot to mid-wicket for a single.

A huge shout for an LBW, but the umpire disagrees! A loopy ball, full, around middle. Nathan Lyon gets down on his knee and tries to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. That was probably spinning down leg.
SIX! The Aussie skipper is on the attack. Flatter and fuller, around middle, Cummins clears his front leg and hammers it over mid-wicket.
Fullish and around off, Cummins pushes it to covers from the middle of his bat. Niroshan Dickwella appeals thinking that it came off the pads. Funny!
Spinning away from the batter, outside off, Pat leaves it alone.
FOUR! Pat Cummins continues to attack Jeffrey Vandersay! Another full ball, around middle and off. Pat Cummins sweeps this towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Shorter, a googly, around middle. Pat Cummins blocks it off the back foot.
SIX! Gigantic! Floated one, full and around off, Pat Cummins goes down on one knee and launches it over wide long on for a maximum. 16 from the over. Lead crosses 100!
Tosses it up, full and angling across, outside off. Lyon tries to sweep it but misses.
FOUR! Lyon and Australia are off the mark on Day 3! Full again, around off. Lyon this time reverse-sweeps it and hits it fine to third man for a boundary. Good shot that!
Slightly short and outside off. Lyon looks to reverse-sweep it but misses.
Tossed up, slower through the air, on middle. Lyon sweeps it to square leg. No run there.
A single now! Fuller ball on middle. Lyon sweeps it hard and through square leg for a single.
Flatter ball, around middle and leg. Cummins stays back and blocks it out.
Fuller ball, tailing on the pads. Lyon whips it to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! A beauty of a delivery from Asitha Fernando! Pat Cummins was rather expecting a short ball but this is a yorker, around off and swinging in. Pat Cummins hangs back as he looks to block it out but misses and the ball shatters the stumps. Good start by Sri Lanka.
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: A mix up but Swepson makes his ground! A fuller ball, slanting around middle and leg. Swepson fails to flick it away and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to covers and there is a yes or no for a quick single. Swepson is rushing to the bowler's end and he makes his ground as Fernando misses his shy.
Full toss on the pads, flicked to fine leg for a single.

OUT! BOWLED! Australia are bundled out! Sri Lanka have done well as they have not allowed the tail to wag much! Asitha Fernando again gets a good amount of inward swing, this is full and around middle. Mitchell Swepson is too late to get his bat down and the ball disturbs the stumps behind. Australia lead by 109 runs.
Howout: b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: FOUR! Sri Lanka and Pathum Nissanka are underway! This is full and wide outside off, Starc tries to swing back in but fails and Nissanka drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
On a length and on top of off. Nissanka gets behind the line to block it out. The ball rolls to covers and a quick single is taken.
A length ball, just outside off. Karunaratne defends on the back foot.
FOUR! Karunaratne is off the mark as well! Full ball, outside off, not much swing there. Karunaratne plants his front foot out and plays a square drive past point for a boundary.
FOUR! Third boundary off the over! Starc misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. Karunaratne helps it away to fine leg for a boundary.

FOUR! 17 runs off the over! A blistering start for the Lankans! Not a good one though by Starc! Length ball, outside off. Karunaratne opens the face of the bat and dabs it through backward point for another boundary.
Sharp spin! This one lands on middle and spins away from the right-hander! Nissanka watchfully leaves it alone.
Shorter and around off, spinning in. Nissanka hangs back and keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, swept to square leg this time.
Tossed up, outside off. Nissanka looks to sweep but does so uppishly and to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Leg bye! Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Nissanka fails to flick and gets hit on the pads. It lobs over leg slip and goes to fine leg for a leg bye.
Flatter and outside off. Karunaratne blocks it out.
On a length and around leg, at 142 kph. Nissanka is rushed as he blocks it out.
Fuller, across and outside off. Nissanka leans and pushes it to the vacant mid off region for a single.
Too full and down the leg side, late swing there. Karunaratne looks to flick it but misses.
FOUR! This is not a good start by Starc. He is failing to hit the line! Sprays one on the pads. Karunaratne whacks it to deep square leg for a boundary.
On middle, tucked to square leg for one more.
On a length and on off. Kept out by Pathum Nissanka.
FOUR! Tossed up on off, Dimuth Karunaratne sweeps it towards backward square leg for a boundary. A good start from Sri Lanka so far.
Goes outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne guides it towards the fielder at point.
Bowls it on middle, this is defended out solidly.
Fuller one with some turn, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to block this one but misses.
Goes on off again, Dimuth Karunaratne eases it towards the off side.
This one lands fuller with some turn, Dimuth Karunaratne gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Tossed up on middle, this is guided towards the leg side for one.
Goes fuller and down the middle, Dimuth Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Fuller again and on off, Pathum Nissanka drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Bowls it on off, Pathum Nissanka pushes it towards mid on for one.
Goes on middle and fuller in length, Dimuth Karunaratne defends it back towards the bowler. Oh, its a no ball.
Goes on leg this time, Dimuth Karunaratne sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Pathum Nissanka guides it to deep extra covers where Nathan Lyon makes a diving stop at the boundary line. A couple of runs taken.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off shaping it away, Dimuth Karunaratne lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT! This one lands on middle and fuller with some turn, Dimuth Karunaratne looks to sweep it but gets a slight bottom edge and gets towards the keeper who takes a sharp catch. The skipper departs at 23 and Australia get an early breakthrough.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Nathan Lyon bowls it outside off, Kusal Mendis defends it solidly off the front foot.
Goes fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off shaping it into the batter, Kusal Mendis goes on his backfoot and defends it away.
Tosses it on middle with a hint of turn, Pathum Nissanka looks to play at it but misses.
On midde this time, Pathum Nissanka defends it back towards the bowler.
This is on off, Pathum Nissanka drives it towards covers for a brace.
Short and turning away, Nissanka cuts it off the backfoot and Head at covers dives to his left to stop it.

OUT! LBW! A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Pathum Nissanka decides to go upstairs. A flighted delivery on the stumps, Nissanka gets down on one knee and looks to sweep it but misses as the ball hits his thigh. Ball Tracking shows that the ball was hitting the stumps and Pathum Nissanka has to walk away. Australia have an early breakthrough and Sri Lanka look in trouble.
Howout: lbw b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary: On off, defended out.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle, Kusal Mendis gets on his knees and sweeps it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Guides a fuller ball towards the fielder at point.
Fuller on off with some tun, Kusal Mendis looks to play at it but misses.
This one lands on leg, Kusal Mendis defends it towards short leg fielder.
Fuller and outside off, Kusal Mendis looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces back towards the keeper.
Tossed-up delivery, this is guided towards the off side.
FOUR! This one lands outside leg, Oshada Fernando uses the pace of the ball and sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Goes outside off, Oshada Fernando looks to sweep again but misses it this time.
This is outside off again, Oshada Fernando defends it away.
Fuller in length and on middle, Oshada Fernando works it towards the leg side for a single.
Much fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis eases it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up on middle, Kusal Mendis looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the leg side. They take a single.
Fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis sweeps it but finds the fielder at backward square leg. They take a single.
Oh, this was close. Fuller and on middle, Oshada Fernando flicks it towards mid on. The ball carries but just falls short of the fielder at mid on. Oshada Fernando gets a lucky breakthrough.

An appeal but the finger stays down. Fuller and turning it on the leg, Oshada Fernando looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads. There was big turn and the replay shows it was umpire's call on wickets hitting.
Turning in on middle, Oshada Fernando leaves it and it brushes his pads and rolls towards the leg slip.
Flighted delivery on leg, Oshada Fernando steps out and looks to go over mid on but miscues it towards deep mid wicket. The ball fell short of the fielder and they take a single.
Dropped! Fuller and on middle, Kusal Mendis flicks it and hits it straight to Warner who gets both hands to it but fails to catch it.
Full and on the off, turning away, Mendis leans forward and drives to point for a quick single.
Full and on the middle, Fernando blocks it straight to the bowler.
Tossed up on the leg, flicked to short mid-wicket.
SIX! Lovely Shot. This was tossed up on the middle, Fernando clears his back leg and just lofts it through the line over the bowlers head for a biggie.
A bit short outside off, Fernando pushes it to point.
Full and on the leg, Fernando flicks it but could not find the gap.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up on middle with some turn, Kusal Mendis looks to sweep it but gets a top edge as the ball carries towards short fine leg. Mitchell Swepson makes no mistake and takes a comfortable catch in his both hands. Huge trouble for Sri Lanka as they lose their third wicket! They still trail by 50 runs.
Howout: c Mitchell Swepson b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: On off and turns it a long way, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to block it but the ball hits his pads. A slight appeal but the umpire seems uninterested.
This one lands on leg, Dhananjaya de Silva sweeps it towards the leg side for one.
Goes on off, Oshada Fernando defends it away.
This was similar to the last delivery, Oshada Fernando again defends it towards Nathan Lyon.

Oh, this was close! This one lands on leg, Oshada Fernando sweeps it but the ball hits the helmet of the fielder at short leg and just falls short of Nathan Lyon who makes a diving effort. Oshada Fernando gets a lucky escape.
Tossed up and on the leg, Dhananjaya de Silava drives it towards long on. They get 3 runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mitchell Swepson is already celebrating, the fielders around join in as well. Although the umpire takes his time to raise the finger. The umpires have a chat and decide to go upstairs to check the bump ball. The soft signal is out. The replays show clear spike as the ball passes the blade. Coming to the delivery, it is full and outside off, Fernando tries to dig it out but gets an outside edge and it goes to first slip where Steven Smith takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Mitchell Swepson

Commentary: Full toss around leg, Chandimal gets off the mark with a sweep towards fine leg.
This one lands a bit short, turning in, de Silva pushes it to deep backward cover for a single.
Full again and on the leg, Chandimal gets down and plays an uppish sweep to the deep square leg fielder for a single.
Sharp Turn! Good-length delivery, turning away from the right hander, Dhananjaya de Silva decides to leave it alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one lands outside off and turns in, Dinesh Chandimal looks to reverse sweep it but misses. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races towards the long stop and behind the fence for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Dinesh Chandimal defends it back towards the bowler.
On off this time, Dinesh Chandimal guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
This one lands outside off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to cut it but gets a bottom edge and bounces through the wicket and past the fielder. They take a single.

FOUR BYES! This was a chance for stumping but the keeper misses it. This one lands outside off and turns in sharply, Dhananjaya de Silva dances down the track to play at it but misses. The keeper also misses it as it races down to the fine leg fence.
Fuller in length, Dhananjaya de Silva uses his feet and pushes it to covers.
Length delivery outside off, turning away. Chandimal plays a cut off his back foot past the point fielder for a brace.
On a length and on off, turning away, Chandimal blocks it out.
Length and outside off, turning away. Chandimal knocks it towards third man for a single.
Full and on the middle, Dhananjaya de Silva plays a slogsweep towards deep square leg. They get across for a single.
A bit short on the off, Chandimal plays a cut off his back foot but could only find the fielder at point.
Full delivery on the middle, Chandimal defends it solidly.
FOUR BYES! Fuller and outside leg, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to flick it but misses as the ball races to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On off, this is defended out solidly.
Shorter one on off, Dhananjaya de Silva cuts it through point for three runs.
This one lands outside off, Dinesh Chandimal reverse sweeps it towards backward point for one.
Touch fuller and on off, Dhananjaya de Silva defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva eases it towards the fielder at short leg.
Tossed up on the off, Chandimal uses his feet to drive it to mid off and gets a quick single.
On length on the leg,turning a bit. de Silva lets it hit his body.
Loopy fulltoss on the middle, de Sliva drives it hard straight towards the bowler, but it did not carry.
On a length and on off, de Silva pushes it to the off side for a single.
This one lands on middle and leg, Chandimal drives it straight to mid on.
Short and wide on off, Chandimal goes on his back foot and cuts it sweetly but could not get it past the cover fielder.

Oh, close again. This was shorter and on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to play at it but the ball hits his glove and falls short from the keeper who chases it. Nathan Lyon is causing havoc for Sri Lanka with his sharp turn and bounce.
On off, this is pushed towards point for one.
This one lands on off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to reverse sweep it but gets a bottom edge and rolls towards the leg slip.
On off, Dinesh Chandimal looks to play at it but gets an inside edge and hits his pads.
FOUR! Fuller on off, Dinesh Chandimal plays a reverse sweep as the ball goes behind the backward point fence for a boundary.
Tossed-up delivery, Dinesh Chandimal flicks it towards mid on for one.
Head starts with a length delivery on the off, turning in. Dinesh Chandimal plays a front foot defense.

OUT! BOWLED! This one turns sharply in from outside off, Chandimal goes for the drive as the ball sneaks in between his pads and the bat and hits the middle pole. The hosts have now lost half of their side and they look to be in deep trouble.
Howout: b Travis Head

Commentary: A loud appeal from behind the sticks but the bowler shows no interest. It is full and angled down leg. Niroshan Dickwella gets low and sweeps it to short fine leg for one. There is some nick on it.
A stifled appeal from the bowler. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Another man bites the dust for Sri Lanka. The umpire wasn't interested at first but is forced to change his decision here. It is looped up, around off, turning in. Dhananjaya de Silva misjudges it completely. He goes deep inside his crease and leaves it alone thinking it would go down leg, although it straightens a touch and causes a lot of trouble. Pat Cummins opts for the review. No UltraEdge is required. The Ball Tracking shows three reds.
Howout: lbw b Travis Head

Commentary: On off, blocked out. What a change by Pat Cummins. Head literally turned this game on his head. Two crucial wickets in the over. Sri Lanka in huge trouble.
Fuller on leg, Niroshan Dickwella looks to sweep it but could not connect well.
Fuller on middle and turns it sharply, Niroshan Dickwella looks to sweep again but misses.
On middle, Niroshan Dickwella sweeps it towards backward square leg  for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Huge trouble for the hosts as Ramesh Mendis walks out on a duck! Fuller with a hint of turn, Ramesh Mendis looks to sweep it but gets a top edge as the ball carries towards fine leg and Usman Khawaja takes a comfortable catch. They trail by 12 now. Jeffrey Vandersay is the new man in.
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Shorter on middle, Jeffrey Vandersay punches it towards covers.
FOUR! Tossed-up delivery, Jeffrey Vandersay reverse sweeps it towards deep point for a boundary.
On a length outside off, turning away, Dickwell cuts it past point for a single.
BYES! Misses everyone. This land outside off, and turns in sharply. Jeffrey Vandersay fails to get any blade on it. Carey fails to gather it and the batters sneak in a couple.
Full and on the middle, Vandersay tries to play the reverse sweep but finds the man at backward point.
On a length and on off, Vandersay drives it straight to mid off.
Full length and on the off, Vandersay crunches it past the cover fielder. They take three runs.
Fuller, on middle and off. Niroshan Dickwella tries to sweep it away but misses. Head appeals but the umpire is unmoved. It clearly hits his gloves, the replays later confirm.
Tossed up on leg, Jeffrey Vandersay sweeps it but gets a top edge. The ball was in the air for some time but falls in no man's land at short fine leg. They rotate the strike.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up on middle, Niroshan Dickwella looks to reverse sweep it but gets a top edge and the ball carries towards short cover where Labuschagne takes a diving catch with both hands to his left. Australia are looking to bag Sri Lanka before Lunch.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: On off, Lasith Embuldeniya looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller one on middle, Lasith Embuldeniya defends it soolidly off his front foot.
This one lands on off and turns sharply, Lasith Embuldeniya looks to defend it but misses.
Nathan Lyon bowls it on middle, Lasith Embuldeniya blocks it solidly.

OUT! BOWLED! What a beauty of a delivery. This one lands on the rough outside off, turns sharply into the right hander. Vandersay tries to play a drive at it but the ball goes between his bat and pads and hits top of middle stump.
Howout: b Travis Head

Commentary: FOUR! Asitha Fernando manages to get some lead on board now with this boundary. Tossed up on the off, Fernando just smashes it over the bowler for a boundary at long on. Incredible hit but comes a little too late.
On a length and on middle, Fernando smears it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on the middle, Embuldeniya blocks it off.

OUT! LBW! That is it for the Sri Lankan innings. This one was full and on middle and leg, Embuldeniya tries to flick it but gets beaten and gets hit on his pads. The Australians appeal for the LBW but the finger stayed down. Pat Cummins goes for the review and it works in their favour, as the Ball Tracking shows three reds to end this Sri Lankan innings. Travis Head steals the spotlight here with his 4-fer in just 2.5 overs.
Howout: lbw b Travis Head

Commentary: Starts with a fuller one outside off, David Warner looks to cut it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces towards the off side.
Fuller one again, David Warner looks to slog sweep it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller delivery on off, David Warner goes down on the one knee and reverse sweeps it towards the third man region for a boundary. They need one now.

SIX! BANG! Here are the winning runs. David Warner finishes things off in style. It is tossed up, wide outside off. David Warner dances down the track, gets underneath it and smokes it over the long on fence to get his side over the victory line. AUSTRALIA WIN THE GAME BY 10 WICKETS!
